# Figma MCP Guidelines

## Core Principles
### Semantic HTML First
- ALWAYS use proper semantic HTML elements instead of generic divs
- Use `<form>`, `<input>`, `<label>`, `<button>`, `<section>`, `<header>`, `<main>`, `<nav>` etc.
- Every form input MUST have a corresponding `<label>` element with proper `for` attributes
- Use `<fieldset>` and `<legend>` for grouping related form elements
- Ensure proper heading hierarchy (`<h1>`, `<h2>`, `<h3>`, etc.)

### Functional Components Over Styling
- Generate FUNCTIONAL code, not just visual replicas
- Form elements must be actual `<input>`, `<select>`, `<textarea>` elements with proper `name` and `id` attributes
- Buttons must be `<button>` elements with proper `type` attributes (`submit`, `button`, `reset`)
- Links must be `<a>` elements with proper `href` attributes
- Images must be `<img>` elements with proper `src` and `alt` attributes
- ALWAYS use figma images hosted on localhost from the figma code, don't use placeholder images.
- When using svg icons, either use the figma code or use the closest lucide icons. Don't create new icons or mess with the existing ones.

### Accessibility Requirements
- ALWAYS include proper ARIA labels and roles
- Ensure proper color contrast ratios
- Include focus states for interactive elements
- Use semantic markup for screen readers
- Add `aria-describedby` for form validation messages
- Include `aria-required` for required form fields

## HTML Structure Guidelines
### Form Generation
- When generating forms, ALWAYS use this structure:
```html
<form class="..." method="post" action="/register">
  <fieldset class="...">
    <legend class="sr-only">Registration Information</legend>
    
    <div class="form-group">
      <label for="fullName" class="...">Full Name</label>
      <input 
        type="text" 
        id="fullName" 
        name="fullName" 
        class="..." 
        placeholder="Enter your full name"
        required 
        aria-describedby="fullName-error"
      />
      <span id="fullName-error" class="error-message" aria-live="polite"></span>
    </div>
    
    <button type="submit" class="...">Sign Up</button>
  </fieldset>
</form>
```

### Layout Structure
- Use CSS Grid or Flexbox for layouts instead of absolute positioning
- Avoid excessive div nesting - maximum 3 levels deep unless absolutely necessary
- NEVER use absolute positioned decorative borders - use CSS border properties directly on elements
- Use semantic containers and avoid fixed pixel widths for responsive design
- Implement proper responsive breakpoints for mobile, tablet, and desktop
- Use `max-width` and responsive units instead of fixed widths

```html
<!-- BAD: Fixed positioning and decorative borders -->
<div class="absolute left-[755px] top-1/2 transform -translate-y-1/2 w-[409px]">
  <div class="relative bg-white h-12 px-3 py-0 rounded-sm w-full">
    <div class="absolute inset-[-1px] border border-primary border-solid rounded-[3px] pointer-events-none"></div>
    <input type="text" class="form-input" />
  </div>
</div>

<!-- GOOD: Responsive layout with proper CSS borders -->
<main class="registration-page">
  <div class="container max-w-md mx-auto px-4">
    <form class="registration-form">
      <div class="form-group">
        <input 
          type="text" 
          class="form-input border-2 border-gray-300 focus:border-primary rounded-md px-3 py-2 w-full"
        />
      </div>
    </form>
  </div>
</main>
```

## CSS/Styling Guidelines
### Class Naming
- Use meaningful, semantic class names instead of utility-only classes
- Follow BEM methodology when possible: `.block__element--modifier`
- Avoid single-use utility classes for complex components
- Group related styles into component classes

### Responsive Design
- ALWAYS use responsive units (`rem`, `em`, `%`, `vw`, `vh`) instead of fixed pixels
- Use CSS Grid and Flexbox for responsive layouts
- Include mobile-first media queries
- Avoid absolute positioning for main layout elements

### Layout Approach
- Use CSS Grid for 2D layouts (rows and columns)
- Use Flexbox for 1D layouts (single row/column)
- Use CSS custom properties for consistent spacing and colors
- Prefer CSS Grid/Flexbox over absolute positioning

## React Component Guidelines
### Component Structure
- Generate functional React components with proper TypeScript types
- Use React hooks (useState, useEffect, etc.) for state management
- Include proper event handlers for form interactions
- Add form validation logic

### Example React Component Structure:
```tsx
import React, { useState } from 'react';

interface RegistrationFormProps {
  onSubmit?: (data: RegistrationData) => void;
}

interface RegistrationData {
  fullName: string;
  email: string;
  phone: string;
  // ... other fields
}

export const RegistrationForm: React.FC<RegistrationFormProps> = ({ onSubmit }) => {
  const [formData, setFormData] = useState<RegistrationData>({
    fullName: '',
    email: '',
    phone: '',
  });
  
  const [errors, setErrors] = useState<Partial<RegistrationData>>({});

  const handleSubmit = (e: React.FormEvent) => {
    e.preventDefault();
    // Validation logic
    if (validateForm()) {
      onSubmit?.(formData);
    }
  };

  return (
    <form onSubmit={handleSubmit} className="registration-form">
      {/* Form fields */}
    </form>
  );
};
```

## Anti-Patterns to Avoid
### DON'T Use These Patterns
- ❌ Excessive div nesting (more than 3 levels)
- ❌ Absolute positioning for main layout elements
- ❌ Non-semantic HTML (divs instead of buttons, inputs, etc.)
- ❌ Missing form functionality (no actual inputs)
- ❌ Hardcoded pixel values for responsive elements
- ❌ Missing accessibility attributes
- ❌ Complex utility class combinations instead of semantic classes
- ❌ Inline styles or style attributes
- ❌ Missing form validation
- ❌ Non-functional interactive elements
- ❌ Fixed width layouts that don't adapt to different screen sizes
- ❌ Missing proper form structure (`<form>` wrapper)
- ❌ Incorrect placeholder text that doesn't match field purpose
- ❌ Missing proper input types (email, tel, password, etc.)
- ❌ Decorative borders created with absolute positioned divs
- ❌ Missing proper label-input associations (`for` and `id` attributes)
- ❌ Non-functional checkboxes (styled divs instead of actual inputs)
- ❌ Missing hover and focus states for interactive elements
- ❌ Hardcoded country codes without proper selection functionality
- ❌ Text alignment inconsistencies (center vs left for form labels)

### Examples of Bad Patterns:
```html
<!-- BAD: Non-semantic, non-functional -->
<div class="bg-white box-border content-stretch flex flex-col gap-2 h-12 items-start justify-center px-3 py-0 relative rounded-sm shrink-0 w-[409px]">
  <div class="font-inter font-medium leading-[0] not-italic relative shrink-0 text-[12px] text-black/30">
    Enter Your Name
  </div>
</div>

<!-- BAD: Decorative border with absolute positioning -->
<div class="absolute inset-[-1px] border border-primary border-solid rounded-[3px] pointer-events-none shadow-[0px_4px_10px_0px_rgba(0,0,0,0.12)]"></div>

<!-- BAD: Non-functional checkbox -->
<div class="checkbox-container relative w-6 h-6">
  <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-primary rounded-[3px]"></div>
  <img src="..." alt="Tick" class="absolute top-[3px] left-[3px] w-[18px] h-[18px]" />
</div>

<!-- BAD: Missing form wrapper -->
<div class="flex flex-col gap-3 w-full">
  <!-- form fields without form element -->
</div>

<!-- BAD: Wrong placeholder text -->
<input type="text" placeholder="Enter Your Car Name" class="...">
<!-- When field is for "Full Name" -->

<!-- GOOD: Semantic, functional -->
<form class="registration-form" method="post" action="/register">
  <div class="form-group">
    <label for="fullName" class="form-label">Full Name</label>
    <input 
      type="text" 
      id="fullName" 
      name="fullName" 
      class="form-input" 
      placeholder="Enter your full name"
      required
      aria-describedby="fullName-error"
    />
    <span id="fullName-error" class="error-message" aria-live="polite"></span>
  </div>
  
